---
// Sitewide marketing/analytics tags:
//   • Google tag  GT-K5LVS96N  → delivers to GA4 property G-XQJRRDCR3Q
//   • tel_click → GA4 event on any tel: tap (phone calls are the primary
//     conversion; star it as a key event in the GA UI once it shows up)
//   • Microsoft Clarity (project nvxprayvfj) → heatmaps + session recordings
//   • GHL / LeadConnector — the lead forms themselves (already embedded in
//     ContactForm.astro) carry their own conversion tracking; nothing to add.
//
// META PIXEL REMOVED 2026-07-10 — the client is not running Facebook/Instagram
// ads. It was the page's heaviest third party: 155KB transfer (55KB of it unused)
// and ~197ms of main-thread time, more than gtag itself. To re-add, drop this
// back inside boot(), after the gtag block, and restore the <noscript> pixel:
//
//   !(function (f, b, e, v, n, t, s) {
//     if (f.fbq) return;
//     n = f.fbq = function () {
//       n.callMethod ? n.callMethod.apply(n, arguments) : n.queue.push(arguments);
//     };
//     if (!f._fbq) f._fbq = n;
//     n.push = n; n.loaded = !0; n.version = "2.0"; n.queue = [];
//     t = b.createElement(e); t.async = !0;
//     t.src = v; s = b.getElementsByTagName(e)[0];
//     s.parentNode.insertBefore(t, s);
//   })(window, document, "script", "https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/fbevents.js");
//   fbq("init", "821915420060205");
//   fbq("track", "PageView");
//
//   <noscript><img height="1" width="1" style="display:none" alt=""
//     src="https://www.facebook.com/tr?id=821915420060205&ev=PageView&noscript=1" /></noscript>
//
// Pixel ID 821915420060205. It keeps collecting nothing while absent; no data is
// lost by leaving it out, and Meta rebuilds the audience from the day it returns.
//
// LOAD THE TAG, NOT THE DESTINATION. `gtag/js?id=…` only serves *tag* ids
// (GT-…/AW-…). A GA4 measurement id like G-XQJRRDCR3Q is a *destination* of a
// tag, and requesting it directly returns a 404 HTML page that the browser then
// blocks (ERR_BLOCKED_BY_ORB). Verified 2026-07-10 in Chrome. Google's tag
// topology for this account:
//     GT-K5LVS96N  →  G-XQJRRDCR3Q  +  AW-16639866068
//     GT-MQBLNJK2  →  G-JTWV3MYGXT                       (2nd, migration-era property)
//     GT-MQJVTX68  →  AW-16710106121
// Configuring a tag fires all of its destinations, so one `config` on
// GT-K5LVS96N is all G-XQJRRDCR3Q needs.
//
// PERF: every gtag("config", X) where X is not the loader's own id makes gtag.js
// fetch another whole ~150-176KB loader (the "&cx=c" URLs PageSpeed reports).
// This file used to load id=G-JTWV3MYGXT and then config three ids — three tags,
// 497KB, ~700ms of main-thread work. It is now one loader, ~176KB.
//
// AW-16639866068 used to be a second destination on GT-K5LVS96N, so loading the
// tag also fired Ads remarketing pings (whose 3rd-party cookies were the only
// thing failing Best Practices). On 2026-07-10 it was moved, in the Google tag
// admin, onto a new tag "Dormant CPR Ads" that nothing installs. GT-K5LVS96N now
// has exactly one destination: G-XQJRRDCR3Q. Note Google will not let you delete
// a destination, only reassign it to another tag.
//   ⚠ Do NOT try to remove Ads by deleting a config line here. Before that move,
//     G-XQJRRDCR3Q rode the AW tag and would have gone silent with it.
//
// AW-16710106121 (tag GT-MQJVTX68) was dropped 2026-07-10: no Ads running, and
// nothing else rode on that tag. G-JTWV3MYGXT likewise — G-XQJRRDCR3Q is the
// property of record (it holds the Duda-era history). Both were feeding separate
// data streams on the SAME property, i.e. every pageview was counted twice.
//
// DEFERRED LOAD: the tag doesn't fire until the first user interaction OR browser
// idle (whichever comes first, with a load+timeout fallback). Keeps the gtag
// request-chain off the critical path so it doesn't inflate LCP/TBT (real users
// are still captured — the idle/load fallback fires even on a bounce with no
// interaction). This is why PageSpeed sees a fast page despite the tag.
//
// Hostname guard: these only fire on the production domain
// (*.carolinaprorestoration.com). On the *.workers.dev preview and on localhost
// nothing loads, so pre-launch/dev traffic never pollutes real Analytics or
// fires phantom Google Ads conversions. Keys off the request hostname exactly
// like the noindex guard in worker.js — no manual flag to flip at go-live.
---
<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    if (!/(^|\.)carolinaprorestoration\.com$/.test(location.hostname)) return;

    var started = false;
    function boot() {
      if (started) return;
      started = true;

      /* Google tag GT-K5LVS96N — one loader, one config. Its destination
         G-XQJRRDCR3Q (GA4) fires from this single config; see notes above. */
      var g = document.createElement("script");
      g.async = true;
      g.src = "https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=GT-K5LVS96N";
      document.head.appendChild(g);
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag() { dataLayer.push(arguments); }
      window.gtag = gtag;
      gtag("js", new Date());
      gtag("config", "GT-K5LVS96N");

      /* Microsoft Clarity (project nvxprayvfj) — heatmaps + session recordings.
         Inside boot() so it inherits the same defer + hostname guard as gtag:
         never fires on the *.workers.dev preview or on localhost. */
      (function (c, l, a, r, i, t, y) {
        c[a] = c[a] || function () { (c[a].q = c[a].q || []).push(arguments); };
        t = l.createElement(r); t.async = 1; t.src = "https://www.clarity.ms/tag/" + i;
        y = l.getElementsByTagName(r)[0]; y.parentNode.insertBefore(t, y);
      })(window, document, "clarity", "script", "nvxprayvfj");
    }

    /* Fire on first interaction (most engaged users) … */
    var evs = ["scroll", "pointerdown", "keydown", "touchstart"];
    function onFirst() {
      boot();
      evs.forEach(function (e) { window.removeEventListener(e, onFirst); });
    }
    evs.forEach(function (e) {
      window.addEventListener(e, onFirst, { once: true, passive: true });
    });
    /* … or when the browser goes idle, so bounces with no interaction still count. */
    if ("requestIdleCallback" in window) requestIdleCallback(boot, { timeout: 4000 });
    else window.addEventListener("load", function () { setTimeout(boot, 2500); });

    /* Primary conversion: a tap on any tel: link (header button, sticky call bar,
       inline links). boot() guarantees the tag is loaded, then tel_click is sent
       to GA4. The event queues in dataLayer even if gtag.js is still in flight. */
    document.addEventListener("click", function (e) {
      var a = e.target && e.target.closest && e.target.closest('a[href^="tel:"]');
      if (!a) return;
      boot();
      window.gtag && window.gtag("event", "tel_click", {
        link_text: (a.textContent || "").trim().slice(0, 60),
        page_path: location.pathname,
      });
    });
  })();
</script>
